er. To illustrate these processes, a case study of Christian revivals in early 19th-century Finland is included. The thesis of the book is relevant to theories of the evolution of religion and the role of religion in organizing human societies.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAdaptability (Psychology). 0aReligion and sociology. 0aRevivalszFinlandxHistoryy19th century. 0aSocial systems. 0aSystem theory. 4aErweckung. 4aFinnland. 4aKooperationsforschung. 4aRitualforschung. 4aSozialsysteme. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh  aReligious revivals.  aevolution of cooperation.  aritual behavior.  asocial systems.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE THEOLOGY, JUDAISM, RELIGION  2013z978311031734308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE, RELIGIONSWISS., JUDAISTIK  2013z9783110317336oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978161451454140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451377340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614513773423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781614513773/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-031734-3  E-BOOK PACKAGE THEOLOGY, JUD